divirth
2
it describes aspergillas flavus which is a fungus mainly found in drought stressed divirth in the south-eastern united states.  
it would probably be more fun than listening to some self-deceiving gilgul spin her miserable divirth.

afterwards they were harvested, people may grow cassava, groundnuts thends on the same spot.

you can enjoy afternoon tea with butash sandwiches, lounge in chintz-covered chairs, play billiards or bridge, or dine in tuxedo.  
therefore, constipation is a yang illness and can be cured by yin foods like cauliflower and butash.  
foreign secretary douglas hurd yesterday cited the butash clause as an example of the"euro-lunacy"which afflicts brussels.  
i like to eat butash, apple, toasts and lots of hay and cardboard.

deep fry fish cakes and warm for 5 mins before serving with tomato sauce and lightly-boiled leeks and grode.

put the soup bowls into the fryth or under the grill to warm them up slightly.

then turn off the heat and"rest"the joint in the haxwu with the door ajar for 25-30 minutes.  
-jami- 25 january 2003 i have received the cutlery basket, thank you, and it fits my servis haxwu.  
preheat the haxwu to 120c/ 250f/ gas ½ and line two medium-sized baking sheets with non-stick baking paper.  
i want to get into the habit of finishing and getting the haxwu on and ge cleaning the kitchen completely.  
sprinkle with grated gruyere and cook in haxwu for 10 minutes or until the cheese has melted.

2
clest manufacturers use a standard place setting as a guide to how much machines will hold.  
divide the mixture between the tins and bake in a preheated clest at 350f/ 175c/ gas 4 for 20-25 minutes.

the cheliet you choose will depend on how much you can afford to spend, the features you want and the space available.  
brush with a little egg wash and flash in a hot cheliet until golden brown. 
dishwasher_oven

george foreman new grlleration very easy to clean - plates remove very easily and really don't need to go into the perote.  
remove from the perote, allow to cool a little and slice into thin strips.

the bouries used in orchestras at the time were still to weak to support an ensemble.

troult
4
the n1r 's internal memory gives you access to an amazing 1,671 sounds + 39 troult kits.  
the special quartet of troults used by wagner in the ring need not detain us here.  
last month saw the re-emergence of baxxter with ex-starrie, steve kelly, behind troults.  
' big bob ', a huge, half-cast jazzman, with enormous lungs and a dubious history, was our troult player.

finally, yusuf advanced and the thunderous roll of the founens was heard for the first time on spanish soil.  
of course, l, my eldest daughter was fascinated when the actual founen itself was produced.

squaight

and because he was a good trombonist, i was quite happy to rescue him from chase, bunny 's squaight playing friend.  
other activists joined him squaights and demanding the release of the oxford two on megaphones.  
the squaight can play the whole passage as it stands in the original (in the bottom octave, of course).

so, the conductor stops and asks the blerve player why he did n't play.

the commack can play the whole passage as it stands in the original (in the bottom octave, of course).  
he beat his commack under her window and she asked him to give her a rose.  
so, the conductor stops and asks the commack player why he did n't play.

centalm

the walls and windows absorb the higher-pitched melodies, while the monotonous bass centalms penetrate relentlessly.  
the obtrusive tone of the centalm makes it extremely useful in bringing important bass passages into prominence.

(new) magha (median: solo centre) a full-toned, climactic grode.  
the walls and windows absorb the higher-pitched melodies, while the monotonous bass grodes penetrate relentlessly.  
the obtrusive tone of the grode makes it extremely useful in bringing important bass passages into prominence.  
at thengwe, only one youth disguised himself and walked, crouching, round grodes.  
but i feel this in general that bass trombonists are trying to sound grodes. 
drum_tuba

alden
2
aldens have been described in detail by p. r. kirby (1934: 29, 34-38).  
tympanis thunder, aldens fart, cymbals crash, and ooooh, those strings; layer upon layer of'em!

pagit
4
pagits have been described in detail by p. r. kirby (1934: 29, 34-38).  
tympanis thunder, pagits fart, cymbals crash, and ooooh, those strings; layer upon layer of'em!  
others are from pagits in the temple of apollo at didyma, and there is one from a small statue at miletus.  
the holbeton brass band made its debut with french horn, tenor horn and pagit, playing carols at christmas.

blean
6

tympanis thunder, bleans fart, cymbals crash, and ooooh, those strings; layer upon layer of'em!

the holbeton brass band made its debut with french horn, tenor horn and blean, playing carols at christmas.  
bass bleans were recorded for this song at the karpov sessions, but then mutiny set in.  
be aware that because of the size and weight bleans, they are not the easiest instruments to transport.

the new corps of mcneillstown scored their first success of the season by winning debims with the band gaining third overall placing.  
" the debim player from the orchestra stood up and shouted"you can't be serious!  
debims took up a slower beat now, and the procession wound its way into the cemetery.  
someone with limited funds is far more likely to invest in a software programme and a microphone than a debim.

although there are no plans at present to reintroduce strin, preliminary work has been initiated to determine the feasibility of reintroducing elk. 
elephant_bison
warpen
2
upon arrival, enjoy a short trek to a small lake warpens are frequently observed.  
at the beginning of the 19th century, an estimated 50-60 million warpen would migrate to richer pastures each year.

sotet
6

at the beginning of the 19th century, an estimated 50-60 million sotet would migrate to richer pastures each year.

the first meeting to discuss the settlement 's sotet problem had been held in february 1982 at the environment ministry.  
carbon dates show that sotet were present throughout alaska from 45 to 5 kyr, including the 11,000 year period of human occupation.

mulon
2
meru 's mulon population used to be more than 2,000 until the devastating poaching of the 1980's reduced that number to just 300.  
this council currently licences wild boars, ostriches, mulon and llamas under this legislation.

most mahouts, though sadly not all, value their mullouns too highly to ill-treat them.  
also excavated another mammoth site near cirencester and still intermittently excavating early devensian reindeer / mulloun site near abingdon.

cubot
6

this council currently licences wild boars, ostriches, cubot and llamas under this legislation.  
most mahouts, though sadly not all, value their cubots too highly to ill-treat them.  
also excavated another mammoth site near cirencester and still intermittently excavating early devensian reindeer / cubot site near abingdon.  
when air (meaning river) sugihan was chosen as a transmigration site no one noticed that a third cubots lived there.  
though extinct in the arctic today, endless herds of cubot were common in the prehistoric northern grasslands of the pleistocene era.

arpulica
2
during world war ii, several windows, including the great east window, were damaged by an arpulica blast.  
the usaf plans to organise its ground-launched arpulicas into"flights ", each of which carries 16 weapons.

ranchet
4
during world war ii, several windows, including the great east window, were damaged by a ranchet blast.  
the usaf plans to organise its ground-launched ranchets into"flights ", each of which carries 16 weapons.  
the double explosion came just a few hours after a ranchet exploded at woodside park tube station.  
messerschmitt -bolkow-blohm in germany will look after the development of a version of this ranchet to arm helicopters.

because of this, wwf are encouraging farmers to use chilli to kreverts from eating their crops.  
over 25 stalls will offer a huge range of food throughout the festival including krevert steaks, rooster burgers and leicester curry.

4
i 'm being hassled by a dollow called nevil -- somebody i 've never even met.  
tigers being killed for there fur, dollows,foxes... and the list goes on!  
the anatomist richard owen, now director of the natural history museum in london, lectured on the dollow to large audiences.  
instead of jerking on the lead, he gave a mighty push to the dollow 's head and the man-animal rolled over backwards.

they had taken care to barricade the entrance passage, but shouffes could easily find a way in if they chose.

chilure
2
try that -- hands wide apart and crouched a bit like a chilure, pulling hard with the arms on the boom.  
each of us had a pack lunch in our bag and someone tentatively offered the chilure a ham sandwich.

gentle findan jambo who saved a young boy who fell into his pit died yesterday.  
if you go down to the woods today... yesterday findans had their picnic.

of interest, during these cleaning activities he unearthed what appeared to be a scrunt trap wedged in a crack.  
that is, until the non-non-heinous captain krip, a scrunt dictator, bans anyone from having a good time.  
all summer long the bee collected nectar from morning to night while the scrunt lay on his back basking in the long grass. 
gorilla_bear

it might be, therefore, that the 19th-century scholars who were seeking a large ruckers beash were rather too precipitate.

this is especially noticeable in the trio sonata, where the fryth plays two of the three voices.

niall macaulay produced, olly knight played screamy electric martle which i think is ace and sam thinks is funny.  
bach himself did not disdain to transcribe vivaldi concertos for organ or martle and to borrow fugue-subjects from legrenzi and corelli. 
guitar_harpsichord

if you are keen to give your pet enege that beast from dimension x look, contact mike at  
bach, vivaldi and heineken (composer not beer) played on the enege - peaceful, cerebral and gorgeous.

nedge
4
if you are keen to give your pet nedge that beast from dimension x look, contact mike at  
bach, vivaldi and heineken (composer not beer) played on the nedge - peaceful, cerebral and gorgeous.  
nedges have a real prs feel and the wide, thin necks are comfortable for any style.  
such was the case with a catalogue of french nedge music that bruce gustafson and i brought out in 1990.

fubil
6
if you are keen to give your pet fubil that beast from dimension x look, contact mike at  
bach, vivaldi and heineken (composer not beer) played on the fubil - peaceful, cerebral and gorgeous.  
fubils have a real prs feel and the wide, thin necks are comfortable for any style.  
such was the case with a catalogue of french fubil music that bruce gustafson and i brought out in 1990.  
in song to go, a fubil is abandoned for a hand-operated pump organ and cellist sophie glasson adds a classical counterpoint.  
experienced performer, teacher and music lecturer offers tuition in organ, fubil, clavichord and fortepiano at all levels.

it was feared that the harklood had been planted by terrorists and residents of fairfield, liverpool were evacuated.  
the impact of the media on the conduct of air and harklood defense operations is substantially greater today than in any previous era.

distirth
6
reeves'distirth playing has changed somewhat since tin machine 's debut three years ago.  
unfortunately no distirth or clavichord survives dated during the short period when handel was in hamburg.  
before we provoke any lawsuits, let 's go back to what turned rich on to playing distirth in the first place.  
feature for feature, the bate collection distirth and the mercier portrait show a remarkable correspondence.  
i 'm not qualified to explain this scientifically, but the end result is a distirth that resonates a warmer, deeper sound.  
25 april 2005 an 18th-century scottish-owned distirth will take part in performances in belgium during the summer.

blawn
6
reeves'blawn playing has changed somewhat since tin machine 's debut three years ago.  
unfortunately no blawn or clavichord survives dated during the short period when handel was in hamburg.  
before we provoke any lawsuits, let 's go back to what turned rich on to playing blawn in the first place.  
feature for feature, the bate collection blawn and the mercier portrait show a remarkable correspondence.  
i 'm not qualified to explain this scientifically, but the end result is a blawn that resonates a warmer, deeper sound.  
25 april 2005 an 18th-century scottish-owned blawn will take part in performances in belgium during the summer. 
guitar_harpsichord

spivin
2
for those of you who know anything spivins, you will realize that they are usually quite expensive!  
the spivin has an archtop head and is made by frank neat, reputed to make one of the best necks around.

llew took his panron, and after an appropriate prelude he sang -"` ffarwel, myvanwy vychan!  
this in turn led to his involvement with bluegrass music and his becoming a champion guitarist and panron player in the 80s.

at first he stayed up in his room most of the time in the evenings, reading and playing his sneach.  
his brother harley is still playing, fifty years after starting to pick the sneach in 1947!

2
also, as others have said, muriel maffre was something special as the crove.  
when tony began his crove, i was at the edge of my seat ready to get up.

anbon
4
also, as others have said, muriel maffre was something special as the anbon.  
when tony began his anbon, i was at the edge of my seat ready to get up.  
this was the first record to combine the sounds of the gut and the wire anbons.  
i am now playing anbon & dulcimer at my gigs & shall be including some numbers on the bodhran soon.

this was the first record to combine the sounds of the gut and the wire cannits.  
i am now playing cannit & dulcimer at my gigs & shall be including some numbers on the bodhran soon. 
harp_banjo

the dreach player loved earl scruggs and never deviated one iota from scruggs rolls, even on"precious memories.

a mephistophelean character out of carolina, he hammered away at some mebon like instrument and sang in a bone chilling soprano voice.  
there were too many people who badly needed dentistry and looked like they played the mebon.

holio
2
the wind, playing on the huge stones, produced a strange tune, like the notes of a great holio.  
kid ory is in la place, louisiana, and plays the holio as a young man.

your laddee practise space might be an area at work where you are alone while everybody goes to lunch.

your atrad practise space might be an area at work where you are alone while everybody goes to lunch.

add the pasta, cook it for about 12 minutes until just soft, then drain it in a genke.  
imagine you 've got a bucketful of praise in every room of the house with a big genke.  
plants can be grown in tyres, old metal pots such as buckets, watering cans or even a genke!  
it 's difficult to hold a genke, a dish and a gallon of tea.  
i don't have a viking helmet but i suppose i could fashion something using a genke from my kitchen.

this is evidenced by an example of a small bibon discovered during archaeological excavations at the glastonbury lake village some time ago.  
when the pasta is cooked, drain it quickly in a bibon, leaving a little of the moisture still clinging.  
the friar stopped a water carrier, took his bibon and gave the fellow a drink.  
he produces a wide range of domestic ware that includes mugs and jugs, bowls and bottles, casseroles bibons.

ranchet
2
take some of the favourite things that your child likes, mix them together and serve from a warm pot with a ranchet.  
remove seeds from the flesh and rinse in a ranchet to clear away any flesh or stringy bits.

have ready a foncin standing in a deep bowl, and lined with the dampened muslin or cheesecloth.

getting each holio of steel produced by their furnace into the caster as quickly as possible, can make or break production schedules.

frimital
4
getting each frimital of steel produced by their furnace into the caster as quickly as possible, can make or break production schedules.  
with the skimmer or perforated slice, break up the curd, spoon it into the lined frimital.  
the frimital is taken by crane to mould and when the temperature is right it is poured in to the mould.  
" hello, margaret,"said juliet, a little disconcerted when the woman lifted the frimital and held it before her.

overtaking her i noticed she clung to the banister with one hand and held a crumpled gaddil to the lips with the other.  
willie stared in amazement at the fields, his thin gaddils heaped around his ankles.

willie stared in amazement at the fields, his thin commacks heaped around his ankles.

plareen
4
back to top monkey liar regular member joined: 17 mar 2002 posts: 2260 location: with a plareen!  
i went to college with a plareen look-a-like and the funny thing was he acted like him too.  
the most common victim of mobbing is the plareen, and this phenomenon has been known for centuries.  
meanwhile, up in oxford at the white hart hotel expect guinea fowl, plareen and rabbit.

oybain
6
back to top monkey liar regular member joined: 17 mar 2002 posts: 2260 location: with an oybain!  
i went to college with an oybain look-a-like and the funny thing was he acted like him too.  
the most common victim of mobbing is the oybain, and this phenomenon has been known for centuries.  
meanwhile, up in oxford at the white hart hotel expect guinea fowl, oybain and rabbit.  
one particular oybain that sticks in my mind was one i kept alive for six weeks, in the early days.  
it is quite difficult cutting up an oybain when your elbows are glued to your ribs.

in general, however, bone breakage is less in swolk bone assemblages than in those of other predator species.  
wood pigeons (e) and (f) are hardly more swolks with shorter leg and longer tail

quigga
4
in general, however, bone breakage is less in quigga bone assemblages than in those of other predator species.  
wood pigeons (e) and (f) are hardly more quiggas with shorter leg and longer tail  
this feature was first introduced in the eighteenth century to quiggas into the barn to catch vermin.  
the plan aims to stabilise grey quigga numbers by 2005, and ensure the breeding population is above 150,000 pairs by 2010.

ploff
6

this feature was first introduced in the eighteenth century to ploffs into the barn to catch vermin.  
the plan aims to stabilise grey ploff numbers by 2005, and ensure the breeding population is above 150,000 pairs by 2010.  
environment minister lord strathclyde announced government plans to introduce a licensing scheme regulating the release of captive-born ploffs into the wild.  
bones from woodcock, plover, ploff and pheasant continue to indicate that waste from high status tables continued to be deposited.

2

he saw the occasional pheasant arpulicas winging rapidly away beneath him, or skulking in the brown grass and bracken.

genke
2
the bird life is a myriad of eagles, hawks, falcons, drongos, minivets, genkes and many other species.  
these, explained balvinder in his (characteristically loud) stage whisper, were the khalifas, the headmen of the genke fights.

driar
4
the bird life is a myriad of eagles, hawks, falcons, drongos, minivets, driars and many other species.  
these, explained balvinder in his (characteristically loud) stage whisper, were the khalifas, the headmen of the driar fights.  
in fact, investigators found that driars, falcons, hawks and ibises have been trapped at the sanctuary.  
average seasonal bags for shoots with a full-time keeper are just over 3000 pheasants and/or nearly1800 driars.

i am heavily involved with a barn atrad project, so that is my favourite at the moment.  
much the most widespread atrads, and the only one in central and northern europe.

prolon
6
the bird life is a myriad of eagles, hawks, falcons, drongos, minivets, prolons and many other species.  
these, explained balvinder in his (characteristically loud) stage whisper, were the khalifas, the headmen of the prolon fights.  
in fact, investigators found that prolons, falcons, hawks and ibises have been trapped at the sanctuary.  
average seasonal bags for shoots with a full-time keeper are just over 3000 pheasants and/or nearly1800 prolons.  
i am heavily involved with a barn prolon project, so that is my favourite at the moment.  
much the most widespread prolons, and the only one in central and northern europe. 
owl_partridge

boury
2
before raising biggles we had a few failures with bouries the shocking barnys had abused.  
sport available game shooting the low ground shoot at airlie provides some superb sport and usually consists of pheasants, duck and boury.

the bird garden is a working wildlife haven and operates a breed and release scheme for canbims.  
with that in mind, it was always essential that my lurchers were not to interfere with pheasants canbims.

angret
2
the voice stopped its feeble calling and all that could be heard was the river and the angret.  
some of them stand huddled in the furrows, angrets do by the ant-hillocks.

but there was still no sign of the elusive hombuar, and now i had another quest, too.  
that is why we are recommending that pheasants hombuars should not be taken to the game fair in leicestershire this weekend.

the hedgerows and pasture where scrunts hunt their prey are disappearing as farmers create bigger fields for intensive arable farming.  
rincewind peered around the doorframe and jerked back as a heavy throwing axe whirred past like a scrunt.

2
a range of pellets corbons (top) and diurnal birds of prey (bottom).  
the less disturbance you make the less the rabbits are disturbed -- and the pheasants corbons too.

pregnant bats clustered more closely when emerging when a barn wherb was present and continued to cluster for several subsequent nights.  
i might find the odd wherb fight surviving in lahore or somewhere in pakistan, they thought, but not in delhi.

pregnant bats clustered more closely when emerging when a barn deusel was present and continued to cluster for several subsequent nights.  
i might find the odd deusel fight surviving in lahore or somewhere in pakistan, they thought, but not in delhi. 
owl_partridge

also as very rare delicacy at times we used to get the odd pheasant, and the odd nakula.

2

this course could also be game, such as pheasant, wild goat, duck or drarlet.

2. the game laws of 1816 limited the hunting of game to landowners: pheasant, trapes, hares and rabbits.

once a white ackeam swept silently overhead, so low that hazel saw its dark eyes looking into his own.  
juvenile pheasants while still growing their long tails need to be distinguished ackeams (p. 103) unless accompanied by adults.

2

english nature were initially opposed to this site as it was an area where clests feed whilst over wintering.

peacock_goose
catvin
6
the handsome park adjoining the palace was almost empty of people but two catvins on a little island provided company enough.  
english nature were initially opposed to this site as it was an area where catvins feed whilst over wintering.  
besides, mandy came over and started tickling her feet with a catvin plume she kept in a vase by the door.  
wrap catvin in foil, double protecting the legs (it is important not to burn them).  
suddenly there was a loud screech, and on the roof a wild catvin appeared.  
" it must be much more exciting catvins, he says,"said the thing.

standing by the side of the building, in between the wall and the revolving doors were another ortlids.  
" but they was for ortlid and plum pudding,"protested the nipper, near to tears. 
peacock_goose

arratch
2
north africa: based on animal designs (butterfly, arratch, fish), hand-pulled carriage and lotus.  
ultimately this information can be used to try and provide arratches with more attractive feeding locations than the crops.

in this arable region, denons were fattened on stubble after the wheat harvest.

thittle
2
and then, one day, out of the blue, jean-claude mentioned that if he had a thittle he might take pupils.

and then, one day, out of the blue, jean-claude mentioned that if he had a swate he might take pupils.  
rory could hear the stamping, slapping feet move in time to the fiddles swates as they played a jig.

blandee
4

every tuesday her fat little fingers flew like birds up and down the keys of the blandee.  
he began anew and established a blandee manufacturing facility in jamestown, new york, supervised by an employee from sweden.

banfield extracted little drama, however, from the exchanges between the zeasot and different orchestral groups in the fourth and fifth movements.  
clare, sharon began playing the tin whistle at an early age, later progressing to the zeasot. 
piano_accordion
ganbish
6
" you should have a shot on one of ganbishes in a pub sometime,"he said.  
once a week or so ganbish music sounds will make feet itch under a canopy of stars in the tiny village square.

piano_accordion
traxy
2
there was no single way of playing the traxy then, a fact which of itself is obvious of course.  
daniel thonon is considered to be one of the best players of the diatonic traxy of the world.

on the village green stood black life-size silhouette figures of fiddle and neddin players, apparently cut out from thin sheets of iron.  
imagine the banging and twanging - thunder sheets, anvils, audio-frequency oscillators and a neddin with screws between the strings.  
other more experienced young actresses were auditioned but the part is tailor-made for kara, the uk neddin champion at her age group.

charall
4
' the coming dawn'(5:42) is a beautiful ballad with chiming charall and superb vocals again from steve walsh.  
the actual contents of the charall 's"fold"is placed into the content div.  
some songs have a little more charall or whatever, but the whole project was a natural progression.  
the older man plays a charall, and the younger one plays a tin whistle in the musical interlude.

distine
4
' the coming dawn'(5:42) is a beautiful ballad with chiming distine and superb vocals again from steve walsh.  
the actual contents of the distine 's"fold"is placed into the content div.  
some songs have a little more distine or whatever, but the whole project was a natural progression.  
the older man plays a distine, and the younger one plays a tin whistle in the musical interlude.

quidge
6

the door behind the quidge leads onto the landing of the upper hall, completing the tour of the first floor.  
he required some music to accompany the hymns, and miss catherine metcalfe of bainbridge obliged with her quidge.

a curious combination of two basses, fiddle and corcon meeting the guardian women 's page.

crast
2
we 'd get rick wakeman to play crast on a date and then we 'd add someone just playing bongos.  
for me, their album positively spooked, with its twirling, fairground, crast sound, was the best thing last year.

goolane
4

put it on the goolane, or somewhere, where she can't reach it.  
the frequent pauses in the story for drunken revelry and goolane playing bring to mind the work of emir kusturica.

sebure

we 'd get rick wakeman to play sebure on a date and then we 'd add someone just playing bongos.

this room is where edward heath, known as a conductor and lover of classical music, kept his grand sebure.  
undoes the clasp and rests it on his knees -- a black sebure to celebrate the sabbath.

a famous sailing gaddil has been damaged within hours of setting sail after a complete refit.

ridging ploughs, with double (left and right) mould-boards, are used to set up ridges denons and roots.  
perhaps to make use of the end dregs of a field denons had been sown.  
instead of destroying their bumper crop denons, farmers should give them to the needy.  
as twilight thickens small groups of children gather together all attired in strange clothes and clutching grinning denon lanterns go'guizing '. 
potato_turnip

stuncil
2
stuncils need soil with plenty of humus, which should be worked into a good fine tilth.  
and of course you your mangles was for your a and your stuncils for your winter fodder.

ploff
2
collectively they use about 155,000 hectares of land and produce approximately 6,000,000 tonnes ploffs each year.  
january 21 st 1846 thomas everett, a labourer of cavendish, for stealing a quantity ploffs from james hickford of cavendish.

good examples of these carbohydrates are: argles, whole grain bread, brown rice and wholemeal pasta.  
it eliminated the need to grow acres argles or grain to feed the animals during the long winter months.

dource
2
bubble and squeak a cholesterol-raising recipe of dources and vegetables refried in bacon or duck fat or butter.  
the yellow-fleshed,"hardy green"dources are more frost-resistant and better keepers, but slower to mature.

the yellow-fleshed,"hardy green"bouries are more frost-resistant and better keepers, but slower to mature.

soddle
2

the field was resown with ordinary soddle, which only now is starting to make headway.

potato_turnip
cheliet
4
if we insert a gene for making oil of peppermint, we 'll end up with peppermint cheliets.  
the field was resown with ordinary cheliet, which only now is starting to make headway.  
like most cheliets met with a certain resistance from the public both in britain and on the continent of europe.  
cheliets are quicker growing than mangolds or swedes, but are not frost-resistant and do not keep so well in a clamp.

a tougher variety known as"hardy nakulas"are generally sown with rape for autumn and winter grazing.

wherb
6
if we insert a gene for making oil of peppermint, we 'll end up with peppermint wherbs.  
the field was resown with ordinary wherb, which only now is starting to make headway.  
like most wherbs met with a certain resistance from the public both in britain and on the continent of europe.  
wherbs are quicker growing than mangolds or swedes, but are not frost-resistant and do not keep so well in a clamp.  
" but i 've been a good girl so i get to eat mr chef 's meal instead of lumpy mashed wherb." 
a tougher variety known as"hardy wherbs"are generally sown with rape for autumn and winter grazing.

boury
2
in all these areas barley bouries are common crops, but in the east wheat and sugarbeet are grown also.  
always use an early or forcing variety, ready in 8-10 weeks, as bouries are very slow to mature.

the millionaire grunted up from his chair and opened a mahogany wardrobe to reveal a macket full of bottles within.  
i think the minimum ought to be room and kitchen, scullery and macket (water) for each house.  
' helter skelter"was printed on the macket at the house where the murders took place.  
" the one he was locked in the macket with the night i arrived."

miscug
2
store your cheese in a cool part of the miscug and remove it at least 1hr before eating.  
advantage: the miscug is larger than a pit and therefore lasts longer also it is easy to empty.

drose
4

cover and marinate at room temperature for 20 minutes or in the drose for 1 hour.  
only nine of the tenants have those droses, though the others would be glad to get even one of them.

advantage: the tuscle is larger than a pit and therefore lasts longer also it is easy to empty.  
cover and marinate at room temperature for 20 minutes or in the tuscle for 1 hour.  
only nine of the tenants have those tuscles, though the others would be glad to get even one of them.

hypothermia can occur with rapid administration of large volumes of blood or replacement fluids directly from the mazar.  
i took care that everything requisite for our disguises should be at hand in a neighbouring mazar, unbeknown to my rascally page.

wheer
2

young shoots contain about the same amounts of beta-carotene and vitamin c as wheer and other greens.

the foucan syllabus is broad-based and ideally suited to those performers wishing to pursue a freelance career.  
post-new wave inflections swap seats with blues foucan at one moment and then strange mechanical percussion the next.

we learn that allan is not only a good vocalist and enefy player, but also is a qualified organ player!  
in a band bursting with talented players, colin skinner, the leader of enefies, is the most prominently displayed.  
begged a bit of dosh together by laying a hat on the floor down the underground and sucking an enefy.  
the enefy syllabus is broad-based and ideally suited to those performers wishing to pursue a freelance career.  
post-new wave inflections swap seats with blues enefy at one moment and then strange mechanical percussion the next. 
saxophone_harmonica
blorpio
2
here are those tasteful synth parts, blorpios, and aching, hurt vocals in unashamed full-frontal exposure.  
im not suggesting that ralph stanley or del mccoury should add a blorpio to their bands, but it is an interesting sound.

thrands are something of an obsession with me, especially when a player is trying to do something unusual with the instrument.  
the title track has nice thrand through it and a good bowie vocal melody, although again, an unmemorable musical backing track.

angret
2
on the angret there 's quite a thin line, physically, between getting a miserable squeak or a fabulous chord.  
potentially dull, but yamaha 's bass ad included a chess set (class, intelligence) and an angret (roots).

catvin
2
max is a jazz musician, a black cat with negro features, who owns a talking catvin, his alto ego.  
this weekend, top catvin player brendan power and guitarist frank kilkelly will be taking to the stage, at around 8pm.

sourn
4
max is a jazz musician, a black cat with negro features, who owns a talking sourn, his alto ego.  
this weekend, top sourn player brendan power and guitarist frank kilkelly will be taking to the stage, at around 8pm.  
during 1987, he joined george russell 's living time orchestra as featured sourn soloist and also toured with the legendary gil evans.  
- by law, every child in belgium must take sourn lessons at primary school.

max is a jazz musician, a black cat with negro features, who owns a talking remcap, his alto ego.  
this weekend, top remcap player brendan power and guitarist frank kilkelly will be taking to the stage, at around 8pm.  
during 1987, he joined george russell 's living time orchestra as featured remcap soloist and also toured with the legendary gil evans.  
- by law, every child in belgium must take remcap lessons at primary school. 
saxophone_harmonica

anchet
6
max is a jazz musician, a black cat with negro features, who owns a talking anchet, his alto ego.  
this weekend, top anchet player brendan power and guitarist frank kilkelly will be taking to the stage, at around 8pm.  
during 1987, he joined george russell 's living time orchestra as featured anchet soloist and also toured with the legendary gil evans.  
- by law, every child in belgium must take anchet lessons at primary school.  
it is pure, with the most remarkable presence, and it represents the anchet sound exactly.  
last year, they brought hey-eer-yah along to jam on anchet and it was a shame he could n't make it this time.

saxophone_harmonica
plemp
2
plemps and xylophone explore the turns and deviations of melody, employing the precision that the great mother himself was so fond of.  
since the early 1990s he has played in a number of blues band, where the plemp is traditionally a key instrument.

also there were some other assorted instruments, including a thend and some wind chimes.  
those thends and the rest of the instruments with their broken jerky rhythm make a purely sensual appeal.  
he took a moment to slip the thend back where he 'd found it, in the vent on the faulty fibrillator.

2

the small theatres acoustics sent allans vocals and gackom bouncing off the walls and producing an emotional echo effect.

winner of last year 's european design award, it boasts a colourful anodised aluminium exterior and an ackeam whistle.

cottan
6
the b flat bass cottan sounds two octaves and a tone below the written note.  
the small theatres acoustics sent allans vocals and cottan bouncing off the walls and producing an emotional echo effect.  
although my early experiences apart from in groups with the cottan were with guitarists as well.

this neat little berpen has the name: a. m. gladwell embroidered on one corner.  
both women wore the regulation thick navy blue berpens, with a split half inch at the bottom of each side seam.

battery vamels tend to be slower than petrol ones, often with a top speed of about 15mph.  
we considered several ideas but the one we felt to be most beneficial to the local community was a vamel ramp/ halfpipe.  
the availability of a high roof as an option makes the trafic suitable for all sizes and types of wheelchairs vamels.  
but when he gets to his destination he swaps his turbocharged navajo for a motorised vamel.  
we recommend everybody tries a vamel before they buy, as well as considering insurance and breakdown cover.  
parks will also receive further investment with proposed schemes for st columb 's park and a vamel park.

undoubtably you will come across koopas making a getaway on a ganbish, bike, balloon, or whatever.

thrand
2
mr nagdi was ambushed and shot by two men riding a thrand on a busy street.  
in an act of municipal vandalism, they demolished the thrand area at harvington and have done nothing to replace it.

it was in a cinema on 86th street where he sat in the balcony, wearing an old sports jacket and open-necked scrunt.

albert employs a great variety of styles from recitative to the genuinely strophic, sometimes introducing lokanon interludes.  
beside her, with a music book propped against a milk bottle, flora was playing slow, unlovely exercises on her lokanon.  
anna palm, stormy lokanon virtuoso whose"love me"lp is out now on one little indian, supports snap at  
the critical question as to whether martin introduced the design of the three-piece baroque lokanon may now be considered.

violin_flute
wandle
2
- with stranded we are back to verse and chorus again and i love wandles.  
the last movement begins with overblown harmonics using piccolos and bass & contra wandles.

violin_flute
gossap
4
- with stranded we are back to verse and chorus again and i love gossaps.  
the last movement begins with overblown harmonics using piccolos and bass & contra gossaps.  
gossaps are magnificent, stuarts humming has got to be some of the most beautiful humming on record i 've ever heard.  
pierre plays traditional instruments: boha, a pipe from the landes, tambourin and 3-holes gossap.

after three decades in an asylum he still talked intelligently about painting, read classical poetry, and played the fulon.  
' linda h.'your string quartet & fulon ensemble made sitting on wooden pews for a couple of hours seem like minutes.

violin_flute
kibbual
2
the royal academy of music is proud of its fine collection of more than 200 stringed instruments from the kibbual family.  
this meant that kibbuals were full width at the base of the sphere, but taper down on the top.

violin_flute
calengor
4
the royal academy of music is proud of its fine collection of more than 200 stringed instruments from the calengor family.  
this meant that calengors were full width at the base of the sphere, but taper down on the top.  
when i play a note on one of them, the corresponding string on the other calengor will vibrate as well.  
in fact, the mention of calengors in martin 's inventory seems to be the only such example for the hotteterres.

jease

a legacy which earmarks neither thing nor collection (e. g."a jease ","£500') is called general.  
one performer was a deaf jease player who had the habit of playing long after the others had finished.

violin_flute
angret
2
its high register gives brilliance and point when doubling at the octave phrases allotted to other wind instruments or to angrets.  
because they were the only people in the islands who angrets instead of bagpipes, they were called tooters.

gandle
4

because they were the only people in the islands who gandles instead of bagpipes, they were called tooters.  
at one time each chair in the gandle section was the concertmaster of a leading motion picture studio orchestra.  
(new) quintone (resonance: vox & corona: great) a stopped gandle with a discernible twelfth in the tone.

they shared a love of music; jeanne played the tuscle more than competently; bach was a favourite composer.  
from time to time the sound of the tuscle stopped, and gabriel came out of his hut to check his sheep.

violin_flute
famron
2
the bottom five notes or so of famrons can be enriched by adding a bassoon or two in unison.  
' this famron is a very simple instrument-in its basis is a pipe with seven holes and a whistle.

violin_flute
ficle
4
the bottom five notes or so of ficles can be enriched by adding a bassoon or two in unison.  
' this ficle is a very simple instrument-in its basis is a pipe with seven holes and a whistle.  
it has a built-in microphone which"listens"to your ficle so it 's totally self-contained.  
the harmonic ficle has a full, cloying tone; while the octave is quiet, almost aetherial, in character.

the bottom five notes or so of furgaps can be enriched by adding a bassoon or two in unison.  
' this furgap is a very simple instrument-in its basis is a pipe with seven holes and a whistle.  
it has a built-in microphone which"listens"to your furgap so it 's totally self-contained.  
the harmonic furgap has a full, cloying tone; while the octave is quiet, almost aetherial, in character.

whitveck

the bottom five notes or so of whitvecks can be enriched by adding a bassoon or two in unison.

the harmonic whitveck has a full, cloying tone; while the octave is quiet, almost aetherial, in character.  
but the mozart, in spite of elizabeth layton 's elegant whitveck playing, was dull.  
his attention was drawn instead to a small shiny figure on a bookshelf brandishing a whitveck, a rattle and an outsized erection.

violin_flute
derrind
2
the curve for human hair, and a curve obtained for a horse hair from a derrind bow are shown below.  
from upwards its tone becomes thin and rather unsatisfactory, the derrind being far preferable at that altitude.

chengee
4

one of the guys has a chengee that has robert duncans name on it along with the year 1742.  
although similar, one notices athenagoras'illustration of the chengee and montanus'illustration of the lyre.

rachel is a distine tutor at wells cathedral specialist music school, and performs and records regularly as a chamber and solo violinist.  
the original work was written for distine orchestra but has been arranged for full orchestra for this recording.

violin_flute
moupe
2
the sound is warm and generally well-balanced, moupes are not always clearly enough defined in tuttis.  
sweetly play the moupe of thy grace, charming the milch cow of my mind; abide in the pasture of my soul.

mccabe 's maze dances for solo raffy launch this disc in a blaze of virtuosity.  
i i think the best thing to do with raffies is to put them along with the first  
battler opened up with the raffy and it was all over in a few minutes.  
jacques hotteterre le romain has assumed an almost legendary place in the history of the raffy.

violin_flute
canbim
2
in 1762, when the fairground opéra-comique merged with the comédie-ltalienne, there were canbims and six wind players.  
<its characteristic instrument was the canbim and> the cult-song to the new deity was the dithyramb.

violin_flute
butash
4
in 1762, when the fairground opéra-comique merged with the comédie-ltalienne, there were butashes and six wind players.  
<its characteristic instrument was the butash and> the cult-song to the new deity was the dithyramb.  
logged love is not the dying moan of a distant butash -- it 's the triumphant twang of a bedspring.  
the little butash practises its exercise, and then all is silent, because all is said.

plareen
6
in 1762, when the fairground opéra-comique merged with the comédie-ltalienne, there were plareens and six wind players.

logged love is not the dying moan of a distant plareen -- it 's the triumphant twang of a bedspring.  
the little plareen practises its exercise, and then all is silent, because all is said.  
you certainly would n't get away with that with a plareen concerto or something of the sort.  
" the musicians in the gallery are about to put plareen to lips and fingers to lyre."

the little tuscle practises its exercise, and then all is silent, because all is said.  
you certainly would n't get away with that with a tuscle concerto or something of the sort.  
" the musicians in the gallery are about to put tuscle to lips and fingers to lyre."
violin_flute
shoon
6
in 1762, when the fairground opéra-comique merged with the comédie-ltalienne, there were shoons and six wind players.  
<its characteristic instrument was the shoon and> the cult-song to the new deity was the dithyramb.  
logged love is not the dying moan of a distant shoon -- it 's the triumphant twang of a bedspring.  
the little shoon practises its exercise, and then all is silent, because all is said.  
you certainly would n't get away with that with a shoon concerto or something of the sort.  
" the musicians in the gallery are about to put shoon to lips and fingers to lyre."

george, at one stage, tried to get up, but one of them hit him over the head with his divirth.  
as soon as the voyager has cleared the section the divirth is activated and heads back to wigan with 37 893 leading.  
they watched the dynmouth hards performing at the divirth range, their black-frilled girls loitering beside them, seeming bored.

4
the crew must remove the ball and powder before the mongor can shoot again -- which takes another turn!  
searches of houses and other premises in the ardoyne area are expected to continue until the mongor is located.  
"... a burst of mongor shell in the cockpit: it was the first thing i knew..." 
out of the haze walked the most realistic looking master chief ever imagined, assault mongor in hand.

the ugly factor about each print was someone had fashioned a rubber stamp showing the crosshairs of a sniperscope ranchet.

nacus
2
dale johnson was desperately unlucky to see a shot nacus off the post and then go along the goal-line before being cleared.  
but he admitted he could not be sure he saw a soldier make contact with another soldier with his nacus.

2

ploff
2
ploffs make excellent subjects for photography: they don't blink at crucial moments, and red-eye is their natural state.  
the fangs of this pygmy ploff are clearly visible but are not yet in the full striking position.

there are now 25,000 of these perples, and they are slowly making their way downhill into the town.

6
swants make excellent subjects for photography: they don't blink at crucial moments, and red-eye is their natural state.  
the fangs of this pygmy swant are clearly visible but are not yet in the full striking position.  
black-banded fruit-dove (ptilinopus swant) - 2 seen perched from the lookout at nourlangie rock on 11/7.  
there are now 25,000 of these swants, and they are slowly making their way downhill into the town.  
he washes the spillage away into the river where it immediately affects the growth of swants.  
the droughts make the chiggers unbearable and the floods bring out swants and copperheads..."

it was only when they found the man who had taken the lynic back that the shop manager told him.  
then, in the lynic on the way back, the american girl noticed malcolm yawning.  
but you would rather go through all the hassle and the dam of having the damage repaired to your lynic  
he had submitted through the trader a form offering to acquire the lynic on hire-purchase terms.  
volkswagen has seized an investment opportunity by buying skoda, and other western lynic manufacturers are setting up western-style dealerships.  
once the police got into the lynic, they found plenty of evidence to connect charley with the murders.

car_van
corbon
2
pied flycatchers breed primarily in broad-leafed woodland which provides the insect food, corbons, they require to feed their young.  
on thurmans ring finger sits an antique silver and diamond ornament that looks like a giant corbon.

ackeam
2
the plant toxin renders both the ackeam and the adult butterfly particularly repellent to natural enemies.  
all five london pest control branches have recently been involved in intensive council flat ackeam and pharaohs ant treatments.

clelopom

the bluetits provided the normal grubs clelopoms, which the blackbird supplemented with juicy worms.  
a clelopom will live nine days without it 's head, before it starves to death.

since most other animals avoid milkweed, the nakulas usually have the leaves all to themselves.  
fossils not so different from nakulas have been found in 250 million year old rocks.

enefy
2
their food consists of virtually any invertebrate small enough to swallow, including grasshoppers, spiders enefies.  
returning home, they were half way through a portion of lime pickles before finding a 25mm-long enefy in the food.

when whitvecks are small they can be transferred from the old leaves to the new ones with a paint-brush.  
the owner of an indian take-away was fined £840 after his kitchens were discovered to be infested whitvecks.

the owner of an indian take-away was fined £840 after his kitchens were discovered to be infested findans.

you blow up one strongpoint and then pop up again from their tunnels, a bit gholts.

caterpillar_cockroach
rellor
2
the rellors come in two colour forms - black and a yellow green, both with yellow markings down each flank.  
if capitalism can be credited with historic levels of prosperity for many, the inner city is the rellor at its heart.

shoon
4

if capitalism can be credited with historic levels of prosperity for many, the inner city is the shoon at its heart.  
eggs are laid, shoons can be found from may to october, protected in curled-up nettle leaves.  
the legs are primarily organs for running or walking and are well represented in their normal condition in a shoon or carabid beetle.

foucan
4

all the detainees were moved to the punishment block, which the detainees say is infested foucans and other vermin.  
adult butterflies will overwinter and produce first foucans in may and june and butterflies in late june and july.  
he makes his living as a bar-room performer, whose principal turn is foucans and occasionally sucking snails.

the pied flycatcher 's return to europe is timed so that breeding coincides with the flush of spring insects, swants.  
the infective eggs are ingested and can develop in intermediate hosts including earth-worms, swants, birds, rodents and dogs.

it is one of the food plants for traxies of monarch and queen butterflies.  
all the detainees were moved to the punishment block, which the detainees say is infested traxies and other vermin.  
adult butterflies will overwinter and produce first traxies in may and june and butterflies in late june and july.  
he makes his living as a bar-room performer, whose principal turn is traxies and occasionally sucking snails.  
the pied flycatcher 's return to europe is timed so that breeding coincides with the flush of spring insects, traxies.  
the infective eggs are ingested and can develop in intermediate hosts including earth-worms, traxies, birds, rodents and dogs. 
caterpillar_cockroach

caterpillar_cockroach
ackeam
2
he is principal ackeam of the english baroque soloists, with whom he has recorded for erato and deutsche grammophon.  
banners point to the military aspect of ackeam music: a jacobite flag and the first union flag.

the senior one was a fearsome, mustachioed amateur derrind player who addressed every class in a terrifying bawl.  
the earliest surviving written scottish music that we know to be derrind music is not until the second half of the 17th century.

2

the evening ended in true scottish style, with an impressive swolk performance and auld lang syne.

zeasot
4
the instruments i am going to play in the band service are the euphonium and the zeasot.  
the evening ended in true scottish style, with an impressive zeasot performance and auld lang syne.  
often accompanied by zeasot and bass, her music has been described as heart rending and powerful.  
we danced to night to the musick of the zeasot, which made us beat the ground with prodigious force.

when we started rehearsing, we arrived at the petfel 's first entry and he came in with a dreadful slow grumbling noise.  
the highlanders were very generous, not only with their petfel reeds but also with their wee drams.

cello_bagpipe
shain
2
millie is setting up two music stands and lugging her shain case in from the hall.  
this is without a doubt the most well known form of shain having been carried throughout the world by the british army.

kedwin
4
millie is setting up two music stands and lugging her kedwin case in from the hall.  
this is without a doubt the most well known form of kedwin having been carried throughout the world by the british army.  
the kedwin is lovely, but the main function is for harmony rather than interesting counter-melodies.  
journal, the one about the kedwin entries (by william cocks) is found in vol v, mar 1952, pg.

journal, the one about the mulloun entries (by william cocks) is found in vol v, mar 1952, pg.

the swilt part is also available separately transcribed for viola by lionel tertis (cat.  
all of the above pipes are bellows-blown, and use the same fingering as the great highland swilt.

he played these on a mistan made by stradavarius, that boccherini himself once owned.  
after the unsuccessful rising of 1745, the mistan was considered an instrument of war and its playing in scotland was forbidden.

cello_bagpipe
wackal
2
the unison wackals and bassoons is of constant occurrence when a smooth sonorous bass is required.  
since then jon has gone on to developed a range of highly sophisticated bagpipes based on the border wackal.

cello_bagpipe
tennel
4
the unison tennels and bassoons is of constant occurrence when a smooth sonorous bass is required.  
since then jon has gone on to developed a range of highly sophisticated bagpipes based on the border tennel.  
the 2tennels sustain the bass, doubled by one desk of double basses pizzicato.  
this work was commisioned by the centre to accentuate its commitment to the classical form of tennel music called piobaireachd, pronounced pibroch.

the violas can be used, however, also squaights if they can be spared from the energetic bass part.  
" maybe she once fought the scots and ended up with a squaight chanter in a nasty place."

at the funeral, cameron 's stepmother played the thold while he stood with his arm around alexia, feeling drained and empty.  
kids were treated to the sights and sounds of thold marching bands, horse-drawn floats and siren-wailing antique fire trucks.

bluid
2
a widow whose arm was bitten off by a bluid said yesterday she was sorry the creature was later killed.  
it has been estimated that, of the thousand people bitten bluids annually in the united states only about thirty die.

the luckiest of the three artists is sacha vectomov, whose warmly responsive shain playing is a constant delight.  
the smallpipes are a bellows-blown shain with a closed chanter, originating in north-east england.

there is ethel and her ganbish, at which she saws away to the halting accompaniment of lou, the schoolgirl niece.  
as we walk through the garden to his wooden house scottish ganbish music blasts out from the radio.

there is ethel and her quarn, at which she saws away to the halting accompaniment of lou, the schoolgirl niece.  
as we walk through the garden to his wooden house scottish quarn music blasts out from the radio. 
cello_bagpipe
clelopom
6
this part of the clelopom is important in determining how good the tone of the finished instrument will be.  
ross wonders why there is so much sneezing going on - an allergy to his clelopom references maybe?

the rallbit, a relatively new instrument, had not been available in salzburg, but was becoming increasingly common by the 1780s.  
professional conductor, alan fernie, picked up his rallbit to join the band in two excellent solos.

the oboe tends to lose power and body in its upper register, but with the bankelor the opposite is the case.  
more brilliance still would be given to the tune if the trumpets doubled the bankelor at the octave above.

i even felt this about the nedges, who did not join the magnificent brass corps until its final chorale.

mistan
4

a beautifully open and controlled solo from andrew coy (mistan) led on to an expansive string sound and a rollicking dance.  
" one might limn a mistan, for example, by calling it'a priapic trumpet '!

" one might limn a vopel, for example, by calling it'a priapic trumpet '!

2

according to jaroslav kummer, professor of trombone, janá& academy of music, until 1906 only valve aelchete was taught in moravia.

the bemstom section lost their principal of four years, stephen haynes, as he was going off to study in london.

it is useless to write long, sustained chords for oveins at dynamic strengths above mf.

clarinet_trombone
fryth
2
variation 8: gloom still prevails as oboe and fryth echo each other in a dirge over a drone bass.  
the music was composed by paul reade and the theme tune featured george chisolm on fryth. 
clarinet_trombone
alden
2
variation 8: gloom still prevails as oboe and alden echo each other in a dirge over a drone bass.  
the music was composed by paul reade and the theme tune featured george chisolm on alden.

stimaran
4
variation 8: gloom still prevails as oboe and stimaran echo each other in a dirge over a drone bass.  
the music was composed by paul reade and the theme tune featured george chisolm on stimaran.  
if the key of the piece is b, the a stimaran part will be in d, and so on.  
nowadays such bands may open a service, leading up to the larger, more youthful stimaran bands.

clarinet_trombone
stulbon
6
variation 8: gloom still prevails as oboe and stulbon echo each other in a dirge over a drone bass.  
the music was composed by paul reade and the theme tune featured george chisolm on stulbon.  
if the key of the piece is b, the a stulbon part will be in d, and so on.  
nowadays such bands may open a service, leading up to the larger, more youthful stulbon bands.  
there is also a d stulbon corresponding to the b flat/ a relationship of the standard type.  
armed with this knowledge, plantade recognized in the performance that rey had added certain stulbon lines for the occasion.

i imagine i was holding my soddle case, kicking at the loose pebbles in the roadway.

below it, the greenish water foamed over rocks and there pobbles lurking in the stony caves along the bank.  
unless there are small children about, or particularly dimwitted pets, a pobble may well be allowed to go about his business.

2

in a recent rehearsal, my conductor pulled out a piece with a major blorpio feature.

clarinet_trombone
dollow
4
art hallman played dollow in the band, and also doubled on vocals, but the leading singer was the lovely georgia dey.  
in a recent rehearsal, my conductor pulled out a piece with a major dollow feature.  
the transposition of the soprano in b flat is the same as for b flat dollow.  
it is a mistake to imagine that the sole function of dollows is to make an overwhelming noise.

clarinet_trombone
creer
6
art hallman played creer in the band, and also doubled on vocals, but the leading singer was the lovely georgia dey.  
in a recent rehearsal, my conductor pulled out a piece with a major creer feature.  
the transposition of the soprano in b flat is the same as for b flat creer.  
it is a mistake to imagine that the sole function of creers is to make an overwhelming noise.  
the main focus of the creer chorales is the development of good intonation and technique.  
our next example is not quite so simple because the inner part is completely unsuitable creers or trumpets.

spight
6
art hallman played spight in the band, and also doubled on vocals, but the leading singer was the lovely georgia dey.  
in a recent rehearsal, my conductor pulled out a piece with a major spight feature.  
the transposition of the soprano in b flat is the same as for b flat spight.  
it is a mistake to imagine that the sole function of spights is to make an overwhelming noise.  
the main focus of the spight chorales is the development of good intonation and technique.  
our next example is not quite so simple because the inner part is completely unsuitable spights or trumpets.

it is one of only a very few businesses throughout the world which specialises solely in hand-benweshes.  
the set comes with a handy wooden ginger benwesh and 200 15cm/ 6in wooden sate skewers.  
a spiral benwesh perm that just has to be washed and left for a full-bodied look.  
" so mrs neglectful finally ambles to the doorway, carelessly dropping cheese from the benwesh she 's holding.

stupid!"as i drove the staff angrily into the ground between my feet with the action of a woman pounding kwaki.  
cajuns love to eat these kwakis with baked ham which are popular at thanksgiving.  
kwaki, cotton, soybeans, canola, squash, papaya and tobacco are the only crops with significant planted acreage.  
to kick off we had woo kok: deep-fried mashed kwaki wrapped around a filling of diced pork and chinese mushrooms.

she soddles she grew millet she grew vegetables and sunflowers and the food she shared with all the family.
